.help-sidebar.help-create
  %h3
    How to create an API?
  %ol
    %li
      Name your API
      %br
      %em
        Ex:
      IMDBMovie
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Enter URL to extract data
      %br
      %em
        Ex:
      %a{href: "http://www.imdb.com/chart/top", target: '_blank'} http://www.imdb.com/chart/top
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Click
      %button.btn.btn-mini.btn-success{href: '#'}
        %i.icon-eye-open.icon-white
        Preview
      to open webpage and select attributes by clicking
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Enter APIfy path for JSON API
      %br
      %em
        Ex:
      %strong
        imdb_top250_movies
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Click
      %a.btn.btn-mini{href: '#'}
        %i.icon-plus
      to add attributes. Enter 
      %a{href: "http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp", target: '_blank'}CSS selector
      or
      %a{href: "http://www.w3schools.com/xpath/xpath_syntax.asp", target: '_blank'}XPATH selector
      for each attribute
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Enter Unique Attribute to get each record
      %br
      %em
        Ex:
      %strong
        rank
      is the unique attribute in
      %em
        \/api/imdb_top_250_movies/:rank.json
.help-sidebar.help-modify
  %h3
    Modify API
  %ol
    %li
      HTML URL is the html page from which data is extracted
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      API Path is the APIfy URL for the API
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Click
      %button.btn.btn-mini.btn-success{href: '#'}
        %i.icon-eye-open.icon-white
        Preview
      to open webpage and select attributes by clicking
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Add/Edit attributes if you think something is broken. 
      %br
      Attributes are selected using
      %a{href: "http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp", target: '_blank'}CSS selector
      or
      %a{href: "http://www.w3schools.com/xpath/xpath_syntax.asp", target: '_blank'}XPATH selector
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      Unique Attribute is used to identify records
      %br
      %em
        Ex:
      %strong
        rank
      is the unique attribute in
      %em
        \/api/imdb_top_250_movies/:rank.json
      %br
      &nbsp;
    %li
      .locked_small
        Locked APIs cannot be edited
